''' Bruckenthal''' ({{Lang-uk|Брукента́ль}}) was a village (a ''colony'') located in what is now [[Sokal Raion]], [[Lviv Oblast]], of [[Western Ukraine]].

The village was established in the course of the [[Josephine colonization]] by German Catholic settlers in 1786.<ref>{{cite book|last = Lepucki| first = Henryk| title = Działalność kolonizacyjna Marii Teresy i Józefa II w Galicji 1772-1790 : z 9 tablicami i mapą | publisher = Kasa im. J. Mianowskiego| place = Lwów| year = 1938|pages=163–165| url = http://www.pbc.rzeszow.pl/dlibra/docmetadata?id=2073&from=publication |language = Polish}}</ref>

In the interwar period the village belonged to Poland, and was a seat of [[gmina]] (a municipality) including several other villages. In January 1940 the majority of the inhabitants moved out ([[Heim ins Reich]]). The empty houses were taken over mostly by local Poles. In the late March 1944 the village was razed by [[Ukrainian Auxiliary Police]] and [[Ukrainian Insurgent Army]], killing over 200 people.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Szczepan Siekierka| author2=Henryk Komański| author3=Krzysztof Bulzacki|title=Ludobójstwo dokonane przez nacjonalistów ukraińskich na Polakach w województwie lwowskim 1939-1947|place=Wrocław|year=2006|isbn=83-85865-17-9|page=758}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Grzegorz Rąkowski|title=Przewodnik po Ukrainie Zachodniej. Część III. Ziemia Lwowska.|publisher=Oficyna Wydawnicza REWASZ|year=2007|page=57}}</ref>

